<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: CLOSE CALL FOR MEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meanwhile, Black, now a creaky 27, is wrapping work on "Shadow Company," which 
he'll co-produce. A horror film set in 'Nam ("a cross between 'Platoon' and 
'The Exorcist,' " said a serious Black), it will be directed by John Carpenter. 
Walter Hill is exec producing. 
</P>
<P>
"And this time," said Black, "I get to be grim." Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</TEXT>
